commit.message:
build a little tool to group the /DataLookupSystem/data/* except blacklist file
can normalize these words
and combine their frequency
and sort by the frequency
output file is: keywords/keywords_all_normalized.txt

usage: python GroupNNormalizeKeywords.py
after putting PreprocessingFunction.py in the right path and so is the PreprocessingFunction.cpython-35.pyc
Just putting the PreprocessingFunction.py in the right path

function for preprocessing

usage:
import PreprocessingFunction
PreprocessingFunction.main() # show you a sample

PreprocessingFunction.preprocessing("I am a good girl") #use this function to preprocessing a sentence
# output should be: ([('good', 1), ('girl', 1)], ['good', 'girl']) which is a tuple that contain the dictionary of the terms in the sentence, and a list of those terms
Merge branch 'rockround-dummyData' of https://github.com/Omar-Riaz/ih8holding into rockround-dummyData

Changed Output

First line is possible categories to ask questions about

Second line is keywords to use

data preprocessing code
input: sentence
output: top n frequent candidate keywords
